				<img alt='' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/8882151e2f68447b4bc641f6fd72c87e?s=40&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/8882151e2f68447b4bc641f6fd72c87e?s=80&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-40 photo' height='40' width='40' />				<cite class="fn"><a href='../../index.html' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Kevin Standlee</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>			</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
				
			<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="index.html#comment-633">
				August 4, 2009 at 19:06					</a>
									</div><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->

				<div class="comment-body"><p>Andrew:</p>
<p>In the <a href="../../hugo-history/1977-hugo-awards/index.html" rel="nofollow">1977 Hugo Awards</a>, there was no winner in the category Best Dramatic Presentation because the voters selected &#8220;No Award&#8221; as the winner.  Under WSFS rules, &#8220;No Award&#8221; always appears on the ballot, and if it wins, no Hugo Award is presented in that category.</p>
<p>There were Hugo Awards in the other categories in 1997.</p>
</div>

