				<div class="comment-body"><p>Kennie, the short answer is that the Hugos are an award that&#8217;s been around for about six decades. They are widely respected in the industry. A large majority of early winners are also considered classics today and receiving a Hugo is often considered a sign that the winning work is a good example of the best the genre has to offer. </p>
<p>The long answer can be found reading and viewing the winning works; this is something many people do. Exploring this website may also be a good idea, we&#8217;ll be happy to answer any specific questions to the best of our ability.</p>
</div>

