				<div class="comment-body"><p>Dave:</p>
<p>Listings for each year&#8217;s Awards are on the <a href="../../index.html?page_id=6" rel="nofollow">Hugo History</a> page. Specifically, the <a href="../../hugo-history/1967-hugo-awards/index.html" rel="nofollow">1967 Hugo Awards</a> were presented in New York City (&#8220;NyCon 3&#8221;). We do not have historical archives of articles written about the Awards.</p>
<p>1967 was only the first time that an episode of <em>Star Trek</em> won a Hugo Award. An episode won the following year as well, and an episode of <em>ST:TNG</em> won in 1993.</p>
</div>

